#
# leela CLI surface (decoded from parse_command
# line at Leela.cpp:28-67):
#   -h / --help               show commandline options
#   -g / --gtp                enable GTP (Go Text Protocol) mode
#   -t / --threads N          number of threads to use
#   -p / --playouts N         weaken engine by limiting playouts
#                             (requires --noponder)
#   -b / --lagbuffer N        safety margin in centiseconds
#   -l / --logfile FILE       file to log input/output to
#   -q / --quiet              disable all diagnostic output
#   -k / --komiadjust         adjust komi one point in my
#                             disadvantage (for territory scoring)
#   --noponder                disable thinking on opponent's time
#   --nonets                  disable use of neural networks
#   --nobook                  disable use of the fuseki library
#   --gpu IDS                 OpenCL device IDs (disables autodetect)
#   --rowtiles N              split up the board in N tiles
#
# Plus #ifdef USE_TUNER tuner options (mature_threshold,
# expand_threshold, beta, patternbonus, bound, fpu, puct,
# uct, psa, cutoff_offset, cutoff_ratio, mix_opening,
# mix_ending, softmax_temp, mc_softmax, eval_thresh,
# rave_moves, extra_symmetry, random_loops) — only
# present when compiled with USE_TUNER.
#
# leela is **Leela Go** — Gian-Carlo Pascutto's
# computer Go program combining Monte Carlo
# simulations and Neural Networks.  Pascutto is a
# major figure in computer game AI (originally
# created Sjeng chess engine, later Stockfish-
# inspired Leela Chess Zero / lc0).  This `Leela`
# binary (lowercase, per Makefile) is the GO
# (board game) flavor — predecessor to leela-zero
# (LZ; AlphaGo-style training).  Speaks GTP for
# integration with Go GUIs (Sabaki, GoGui).  75
# GH stars.  Sister tools: leela-zero (cleaner
# AlphaGo-Zero-style engine), katago (modern
# Go AI), lc0 (Leela Chess Zero — chess variant
# of the same concept).
